564	\subsection{Use in Serre finiteness}
565	
566	For a proper geometrically integral curve \(C\) over \(k\), a two-affine cover with affine intersection always exists. The bundle \(S\) then feeds the Serre-finiteness chain:
567	\begin{enumerate}
568	  \item The Mayer--Vietoris LES applied to \(S\) and \(\mathcal O_C\) relates \(H^0\) and \(H^1\) of \(C\), \(U_1\), \(U_2\), and \(U_1 \cap U_2\).
569	  \item The cover hypothesis identifies the fourth corner with the whole curve.
570	  \item Affineness of the pieces collapses \(H^{>0}\) on those pieces, reducing the LES to a three-term sequence.
571	  \item Finiteness of each \(H^0\) piece then implies finiteness of \(H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)\).
572	\end{enumerate}
573	Steps~1--2 are supplied by this section; Steps~3--4 are deferred to subsequent sections.
